				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: gravestone of dire melodies<a name="28128"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 16 04 1:30 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>My 2 Cents on this, I've had this augment for a number of levels.  Here is how I use it.  Instead of using up a type 3 slot on a piece of armor that is critical to me, I put it on the 10pt &quot;Sculptor's Hoop&quot; that you can buy form the Nro camp.  This allows me to swap it into my ear slot when I need a wind instrament instead of giving up one of my handy weapon/instraments (BDMG and Tmace).  What I really use it for most other than iniv (since I like my clicky lev, SAC, and invis song much much better than seleo song of travel) is to increase the number of diease and curse counters I can kick off per tick.  Singing my cure song without the earring requires me to sing it twice to cure most ldon trap poisons (you know those nasty kill your group kind of things) but only once with the earring on.  This has saved my party on more than one occaision.
<br />

<br />
So, I think this augment is quite useful pre-epic, but should not take up a type 3 slot that is on a piece of equipment you aren't comfortable swapping out.
<br />

<br />
For me the earring option was perfect.
<br />

<br />
ps, check my magelo below to see the earring and augment in my gear bag.</span></td>
